cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about language modeling using recurrent neural networks with attention-based memory selection. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses regularization techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel architecture for RNNs, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions visualizing the attention mechanism, which could indicate a connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
